statistics.name: assists
statistics.description: The number of times a player who passes the ball to a teammate in a way that leads to a score by field goal, meaning that he or she was "assisting" in the basket. There is some judgment involved in deciding whether a passer should be credited with an assist.

statistics.name: turnovers
statistics.description: The number of times a player loses possession to the other team.

statistics.name: minutes

statistics.name: assistTurnoverRatio
statistics.description: The average number of assists a player or team records per turnover

statistics.name: rebounds

article.headline: IPFW 79, Indiana - East 36
article.story: FORT WAYNE, Ind. -- Nick Daniels, Ben Botts, David Carson and Deilvez Yearby each scored 11 points as Indiana-Purdue-Fort Wayne defeated Indiana-East 79-36 on Tuesday night. IPFW (2-2) shot 49 percent from the field as 11 different Mastodons scored. Cory Sitton led East (7-4) with eight points. IPFW led 35-17 at halftime. The Mastodons held the Red Wolves to 29 percent shooting before the break. IPFW shot 56 percent in the second half to extend the lead. The final margin of 43 points was the Mastodons' largest lead. IPFW outrebounded the Red Wolves 38-25 and outscored them 10-1 from the free-throw line. The Mastodons shot 9-for-21 from 3-point range. Daniels and Botts both went 3-for-5 from beyond the arc.
